Three people have been arrested in Panorama near Cape Town for being in possession of a large quantity of abalone. The police’s flying squad reacted to a tip-off from a community member and searched a residence in the area, where they arrested the two men and a woman. Police spokesperson Andre Traut, says the trio will make an appearance in the Parow Magistrate’s Court on Monday. He says the value of the abalone is yet to be determined. 